  "body": "**Here's the use case we want to enable:** \n\nFirst use \n- user purchases a keycard \n- he taps the keycard \n- this prompts download of the app \n\nOnce app is installed \n- tapping the card on the phone should not pop-up the app \n\n**Constraint** \n- should work with android and iOS \n\n**(for note) Issue with past release of this feature**\n- worked only on android \n- 'First use' case was working as described here \n- once app is installed, the app was still prompted in the following case : if the app stoped listening to nfc, then the app was still triggered. Possible tricks to solve this:\n a/ once app is installed delete the ndef record of the card, \n b/ or get this even done at the applet level in the initialize command. \nNeither a/ or b/ are really satisfactory",
